  Polygon Game ‚ÄĒ Project Summary

  Polygon is a web-based action/tower-defense game where you play as a polygon
  character fighting waves of geometric enemies. It's a client-server game with
  a sophisticated anti-cheat system.

  ---
  Tech Stack

  Frontend (React + Vite + TypeScript):
  - React Router for navigation (login, game, settings pages)
  - Phaser 3 game engine embedded in React
  - Tailwind CSS for styling
  - Mobile touch controls (custom implementation, not Phaser native)
  - Attack types: Flame, Laser, Spinner, Zapper

  Backend (FastAPI + MongoDB):
  - JWT authentication (bcrypt)
  - Anti-cheat wave validation system
  - Upgrade system (~100 upgrades)
  - Run/save management

  ---
  Core Architecture

  Frontend (http://localhost:3000)
    ‚Üď HTTP API
  Backend (FastAPI on port 8000)
    ‚Üď MongoDB
    - player_stats
    - game_saves
    - runs (canonical saves)
    - flagged_waves (anti-cheat flags)

  ---
  Key Systems

  1. Wave Validation / Anti-Cheat:
  - Server generates 30-second wave start tokens
  - Client uploads frame data, kills, damage, enemy deaths
  - Backend validates: movement, damage, kills, upgrade usage
  - Flags suspicious activity with severity levels (LOW ‚Üí CRITICAL)
  - Critical flags trigger auto-ban

  2. Upgrade System:
  - Types: stat modifiers, effects, variants, abilities
  - Dependencies, conflicts, stackability rules
  - Backend validates upgrade selection

  3. Enemy Types:
  - Triangle, Square, Pentagon, Hexagon, Octagon, Dodecahedron
  - Super variants (sprint, shield, spray attacks)
  - Boss enemies (phases: dash ‚Üí idle ‚Üí storm ‚Üí death)

  ---
  Current State / TODO Items

  Gameplay:
  - Progression fixed for first 30 waves
  - Bosses added to first phase, need phase 2 implementation
  - Bosses start appearing regularly after wave 30
  - Special attacks (flame, laser, spinner, zapper) implemented
  - Sound effects for abilities need work

  Mobile:
  - Touch controls in TouchControlManager.ts
  - Layout adapts to portrait/landscape (H > 500 threshold)
  - Needs: remove fullscreen button, improve zoom, button layout customization

  Security (Critical Issues):
  - Hardcoded JWT secret key (needs env var)
  - No MongoDB authentication enabled
  - Debug mode enabled in production
  - Weak password policy (6 chars minimum)
  - 24-hour JWT expiry (too long)

  Features Pending:
  - Leaderboard UI (backend exists, frontend not built)
  - Per-game record: game ID, full upgrade order, enemies killed, total time
  - Additional difficulties beyond Normal
  - Settings system implementation
  - Visual polish: dust effects, color customization

  ---
  Files of Note

  Frontend:
  - TouchControlManager.ts ‚ÄĒ mobile touch input (not Phaser native)
  - WaveValidation.ts ‚ÄĒ client-side anti-cheat data collection
  - MainScene.ts ‚ÄĒ main game scene with wave validation integration
  - UpgradeSystem.ts ‚ÄĒ upgrade logic

  Backend:
  - app/services/wave_service.py ‚ÄĒ wave validation business logic
  - app/core/upgrade_data.py ‚ÄĒ upgrade definitions (~100)
  - app/core/enemy_data.py ‚ÄĒ enemy health/spawn rules
  - app/api/waves.py ‚ÄĒ wave API endpoints

  Documentation:
  - MAINSCENE_INTEGRATION_PATCH.md ‚ÄĒ how wave validation integrates into
  MainScene
  - backend/ANTI_CHEAT_SYSTEM.md ‚ÄĒ complete anti-cheat documentation
  - backend/IMPLEMENTATION_GUIDE.md ‚ÄĒ setup instructions

